-- Cotton, Sugar on Zhengzhou Exchange Drop as China Moves to Control Prices
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-26T02:01:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-26/cotton-sugar-on-zhengzhou-exchange-drop-as-china-moves-to-control-prices.html
Cotton for September delivery on the
Zhengzhou Commodity Exchange dropped by the exchange-set 5
percent daily limit to 24,320 yuan a metric ton after China
broadened efforts to curb speculation and damp price gains.  Sugar for delivery in the same month declined as much as
3.2 percent to 6,219 yuan a ton.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 rdobson4@bloomberg.net  